Adds the option to create non focusable windows in Windows.

Now you are able to use focusable property on tauri.conf.json.

Default behaviour is focusable:true.

focusable:false will create a non focusable window.

"app": {
    "windows": [
      {
        "title": "demoapp",
        "width": 800,
        "height": 600,
        "focusable":false,
      }
    ],
  },

The feature was requested in https://github.com/tauri-apps/tauri/issues/11130

